Program: Omnibus
Title: Chimps
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jwc
Last Broadcast Date: 12 June 1990
A look at efforts being made to save chimps from extinction including a visit to Monkey World in Dorset, UK and interviews with Jim Cronin, James Martin Jones and Dr Jane Goodall on the problems and possible solutions to protecting chimpanzees. Picture: Young chimpanzee, Credit: Getty Images